    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Atomic number of $$\\mathrm{Mn}, \\mathrm{Fe}$$ and $$\\mathrm{Co}$$ are 25, 26 and 27 respectively. Which of the following inner orbital octahedral complex ions are diamagnetic?</p>\n<p>I. $$\\left[\\mathrm{CO}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_6\\right]^{3+}$$</p>\n<p>II. $$\\left[\\mathrm{Mn}(\\mathrm{CN})_6\\right]^{3-}$$</p>\n<p>III. $$\\left[\\mathrm{Fe}(\\mathrm{CN})_6\\right]^{4-}$$</p>\n<p> IV. $$\\left[\\mathrm{Fe}(\\mathrm{CN})_6\\right]^{3-}$$</p>\n<p>Choose the correct option.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "II and III"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "I and IV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "I and III"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "II and IV"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$\\left[\\mathrm{Co}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_6\\right]^{3+}$$ and $$\\left[\\mathrm{Fe}(\\mathrm{CN})_6\\right]^{4-}$$, inner orbital complex ions are diamagnetic.</p>\n<p>$$\\left[\\mathrm{Co}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_6\\right]^{3+}$$ oxidation state of $$\\mathrm{Co}$$ in is +3.</p>\n<p>Electronic configuration of $$\\mathrm{Co}^{3+}=[\\mathrm{Ar}] 3 d^6$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltmn3p3l/c0aefa69-5276-4055-ba33-7b86acd927d1/7b052410-df7b-11ee-bda5-a3731e814987/file-1ltmn3p3m.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltmn3p3l/c0aefa69-5276-4055-ba33-7b86acd927d1/7b052410-df7b-11ee-bda5-a3731e814987/file-1ltmn3p3m.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2023 Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>As NH$$_3$$ is a strong field ligand thus, pairing of electrons takes place.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltmn4nz9/8cb1cecd-14f9-4c46-8117-00a657fed35f/95f6b950-df7b-11ee-bda5-a3731e814987/file-1ltmn4nza.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltmn4nz9/8cb1cecd-14f9-4c46-8117-00a657fed35f/95f6b950-df7b-11ee-bda5-a3731e814987/file-1ltmn4nza.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2023 Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>In $$\\left[\\mathrm{Fe}(\\mathrm{CN})_6\\right]^{4-}$$ oxidation state of $$\\mathrm{Fe}$$ is +2. E.C of $$\\mathrm{Fe}^{2+}=[\\mathrm{Ar}] 3 d^6$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltmn89r0/6fcf18c2-32a4-43b9-82e7-cb178cd47f9b/fa3569c0-df7b-11ee-bda5-a3731e814987/file-1ltmn89r1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltmn89r0/6fcf18c2-32a4-43b9-82e7-cb178cd47f9b/fa3569c0-df7b-11ee-bda5-a3731e814987/file-1ltmn89r1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2023 Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 3\"></p>",
