  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which type of isomerism is exhibited by $$\\left[\\mathrm{Co}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_4 \\mathrm{Cl}_2\\right]^{+}$$?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Geometrical isomerism\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Optical isomerism\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "lonisation isomerism\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Linkage isomerism"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Geometrical isomerism is shown by $$\\left[\\mathrm{Co}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_4 \\mathrm{Cl}_2\\right]^{+}$$ complex as it is octahedral complex with formula $$\\left[\\mathrm{MX}_2 \\mathrm{~L}_4\\right]$$. The given complex have 2 isomers, i.e., cis and trans.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lu28zca3/a8b525b0-6b45-4357-9b32-e07d6be4b27e/cc769bb0-e810-11ee-9416-0f370c03dd62/file-1lu28zca4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lu28zca3/a8b525b0-6b45-4357-9b32-e07d6be4b27e/cc769bb0-e810-11ee-9416-0f370c03dd62/file-1lu28zca4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2022 Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>",
