    "explanation": "<p>In $$\\mathrm{Ni}(\\mathrm{CN})_4, \\mathrm{Ni}$$ is in $$d s p^2$$ hybridised and the shape is square planar.</p>\n<p>The square planar geometry results diamagnetic magnetism as all the electrons are paired resulting in zero spin.</p>",
